      },
      "date": "2013-01-10 17:24:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe commit comment should always include a proper description of the change and not just some URLs to patches which may not exist in the future. Unfortunately, even the commit comment if the original version of this patch is just a couple if URLs to other patches, so one has to traverse three levels if web pages to find out what this patch is supposed to be doing. \n\nIt is fine to include the original change numbers as additional information, but the current comment doesn't explain anything about what the patch actually does. Please copy the comments from the original patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bfb07572ac763da8ae54adeab0897b5db98352f0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-10 17:26:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlso, instead of referring to the master version of the patch by the change number, it is better to use the git commit hash (or both, if you want), which will always exist in the git repository.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
